depression and lonliness i was diagnosed about a year ago with clinical depression and have been on a variety of medications since none which have worked very well i am constantly sad lonely and tired in this time one of my family members that i love got very sick a year relationship ended and just last week my boyfriend broke up with me i am beginning to think i am just a crappy person to be around then today my mom and another adult friend let my sister be a real jerk to me and didn't stop her when i asked them y they are so much harder on me than her they said because i am lazy don't get things done and am worthless and that they'd be harder on her if they needed to be but that she does everything she's supposed to which is a complete lie what can i do i am feeling so horrible i need help but i hate talking to friends about it b c i feel whiny and like i am being a miserable friend please any help would be great if you feel depressed and lonely all the time then your meds may be off you do not mention your age but meds can change with age especially if you are young do not give up on life almost everybody that has problem with depression learns how to manage it as they get older you will learn better what you particular difficulties relate to like seasons new social settings etc i have some problems with depression usually in the winter and i have a few strategies for helping myself giving myself things to look forward to confiding with my spouse and just generally cutting myself some slack all help me a lot of girls feel that they are supposed to be perfect in every way in order for others to accept them don't buy into that i suggest you phone your doctor and tell some of the things that have happened and he she may suggest you come in for a reeval of your meds you will get through this and come out a strong person try reading a biography lincoln suffered terribly from depression if you like historical figures almost every person who accomplished important thing